Instagram on Thursday announced the release of a new feature, Remix, making it able to remix all video content on the platform, in addition to Reels. This will give people new ways to showcase their creativity, collaborate with each other, and still have the ability to reach new audiences on the platform. Over the past few months, Instagram enthusiastically watched the way the community has embraced the Remix feature on Reels, and it is excited to expand the feature to other video formats on the platform This will give creators yet another way to reinvent their content, and collaborate with other creators. As with Remix for Reels, people will have access to a variety of creative tools for remixing other videos, including collabs, voiceover, effects and audio tools. So how do you use Remix? It's quite simple. 1. Choose a public Instagram video 2. Tap the three dots in the upper right corner 3. Select “Remix this video” 4. Record your answer or upload from camera roll 5. A remix of an Instagram video will be visible anywhere you share Reels As for videos published on Instagram prior to this update are not eligible for remix. From today, Instagram will also allow people to highlight information such as the topic, date and time of a scheduled Live on their profiles. With the feature turned on, it will be even easier for fans and followers to view and sign up for reminders of scheduled Lives from their favorite creators. Currently, only the scheduled Live closest to the broadcast will be displayed on the profile. In addition, the tool also eliminates the need to include a feed post with scheduled Lives, although it is still possible if the user wants to.